{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Symbolic Jacobian and Stability Analysis\n\nThis notebook demonstrates the **symbolic-numeric bridge** for dynamical\nsystems analysis. We use Maxima's `diff()` to derive Jacobian matrices\nexactly, `solve()` to find equilibrium points, and `np_eig` to compute\neigenvalues numerically for stability classification.\n\nThe workflow is: symbolic differentiation -> symbolic algebra -> numeric\neigenvalues -> visualization. Each step leverages the right tool for the job.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 85,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## The Jacobian [S+N]\n\nConsider a predator-prey variant:\n\n$$\\dot{x} = x(1-x) - xy \\qquad \\dot{y} = y(x - 1)$$\n\nHere $x$ is the prey population (with logistic self-limitation) and $y$\nis the predator. We compute the Jacobian matrix symbolically using\n`diff()`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Define the system */\nf1 : x*(1 - x) - x*y$\nf2 : y*(x - 1)$\n\n/* Compute the Jacobian symbolically */\nJ : matrix(\n  [diff(f1, x), diff(f1, y)],\n  [diff(f2, x), diff(f2, y)]\n);\n\nprint(\"Jacobian:\")$\nJ;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 86,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "matrix([-y-2*x+1,-x],[y,x-1])\nJacobian:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi -y-2\\,x+1&-x\\cr y&x-1\\cr \\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 86,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Fixed Points [S+N]\n\nEquilibria are where both $\\dot{x} = 0$ and $\\dot{y} = 0$ simultaneously.\nMaxima's `solve()` finds them exactly.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Find all equilibrium points */\nfps : solve([f1 = 0, f2 = 0], [x, y]);\n\nprint(\"Fixed points:\")$\nfor fp in fps do print(fp)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 87,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[[x = 0,y = 0],[x = 1,y = 0]]\nFixed points:\n[x = 0,y = 0]\n[x = 1,y = 0]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Stability Classification [S+N]\n\nFor each fixed point, we substitute into the Jacobian and compute\neigenvalues. The eigenvalues determine stability:\n\n- Both eigenvalues have negative real part: **stable** (node or spiral)\n- Both positive: **unstable**\n- Mixed signs: **saddle point**\n\nWe use Maxima's `eigenvalues()` for the symbolic case and `np_eig` for\nthe numeric case.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Evaluate Jacobian at each fixed point and classify */\nfor fp in fps do block(\n  [J_fp, ev_list, re1, re2, cl],\n  J_fp : subst(fp, J),\n  ev_list : first(eigenvalues(J_fp)),\n  re1 : float(realpart(ev_list[1])),\n  re2 : float(realpart(ev_list[2])),\n  cl : if is(re1 < 0 and re2 < 0) then \"STABLE\"\n       elseif is(re1 > 0 and re2 > 0) then \"UNSTABLE\"\n       elseif is(re1 * re2 < 0) then \"SADDLE\"\n       else \"MARGINAL / CENTRE\",\n  print(\"--- Fixed point:\", fp, \"---\"),\n  print(\"  J =\", J_fp),\n  print(\"  Eigenvalues =\", ev_list),\n  print(\"  Classification:\", cl)\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 88,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "--- Fixed point: [x = 0,y = 0] ---\n  J = matrix([1,0],[0,-1])\n  Eigenvalues = [-1,1]\n  Classification: SADDLE\n--- Fixed point: [x = 1,y = 0] ---\n  J = matrix([-1,-1],[0,0])\n  Eigenvalues = [-1,0]\n  Classification: MARGINAL / CENTRE"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Numeric Eigenvalues with np_eig\n\nFor more complex systems where symbolic eigenvalues may not simplify,\nwe can evaluate the Jacobian numerically and use `np_eig` from the\nnumerics package (wrapping LAPACK's dgeev).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Numeric eigenvalue computation at (1, 0) using np_eig */\nJ_at_10 : float(subst([x=1, y=0], J))$\nprint(\"J at (1,0) =\", J_at_10)$\n\nA_np : ndarray(J_at_10)$\n[vals, vecs] : np_eig(A_np)$\nprint(\"Eigenvalues (numeric):\", np_to_list(vals))$\nprint(\"Eigenvectors:\")$\nnp_to_matrix(vecs);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 89,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "J at (1,0) = matrix([-1.0,-1.0],[0.0,0.0])\nEigenvalues (numeric): [-1.0,0.0]\nEigenvectors:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 1.0&-0.7071067811865475\\cr 0.0&0.7071067811865475\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 89,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Phase Portrait\n\nThe vector field shows the flow of the dynamical system at every point.\nStreamlines trace trajectories from various initial conditions, revealing\nthe global behaviour around the fixed points.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Vector field of the predator-prey system */\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"#cccccc\", ngrid=12,\n  ax_vector_field(f1, f2, x, -0.5, 2.5, y, -0.5, 2.5),\n  title=\"Predator-Prey: Vector Field\",\n  xlabel=\"x (prey)\", ylabel=\"y (predator)\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 90,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
