    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Van der Pol Oscillator [S+N]\n\nThe Van der Pol oscillator is a classic nonlinear system with a limit cycle:\n\n$$\\dot{x} = y \\qquad \\dot{y} = \\mu(1 - x^2)y - x$$\n\nFor $\\mu > 0$ the origin is an unstable spiral, and trajectories converge\nto a stable limit cycle. We derive the Jacobian symbolically, compute\neigenvalues at the origin, and visualize the limit cycle.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Van der Pol system with mu = 1 */\nmu : 1$\ng1 : y$\ng2 : mu*(1 - x^2)*y - x$\n\n/* Symbolic Jacobian */\nJ_vdp : matrix(\n  [diff(g1, x), diff(g1, y)],\n  [diff(g2, x), diff(g2, y)]\n);\n\nprint(\"Van der Pol Jacobian:\")$\nJ_vdp;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 92,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "matrix([0,1],[-(2*x*y)-1,1-x^2])\nVan der Pol Jacobian:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 0&1\\cr -\\left(2\\,x\\,y\\right)-1&1-x^2\\cr \\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 92,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Evaluate at the origin — the only fixed point */\nJ_vdp_origin : subst([x=0, y=0], J_vdp)$\nprint(\"J at origin:\", J_vdp_origin)$\n\n/* Symbolic eigenvalues */\nevals_vdp : eigenvalues(J_vdp_origin);\nprint(\"Eigenvalues:\", evals_vdp[1])$\n\n/* Numeric check via np_eig */\nA_vdp : ndarray(float(J_vdp_origin))$\n[vals_vdp, vecs_vdp] : np_eig(A_vdp)$\nprint(\"Eigenvalues (numeric):\", np_to_list(vals_vdp))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 93,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "J at origin: matrix([0,1],[-1,1])\n[[-((sqrt(3)*%i-1)/2),(sqrt(3)*%i+1)/2],[1,1]]\nEigenvalues: [-((sqrt(3)*%i-1)/2),(sqrt(3)*%i+1)/2]\nEigenvalues (numeric):\n                      [0.8660254037844386*%i+0.49999999999999994,\n                       0.49999999999999994-0.8660254037844386*%i]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The eigenvalues at the origin have **positive real part** ($\\mu/2 > 0$),\nconfirming the origin is an unstable spiral. All nearby trajectories\nspiral outward — but they are captured by the **stable limit cycle**.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Phase portrait of the Van der Pol oscillator */\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"#dddddd\", ngrid=12,\n  ax_vector_field(g1, g2, x, -4, 4, y, -4, 4),\n  color=\"#377eb8\",\n  initial_points=[[0.1, 0.0], [3.5, 0.0], [0.0, 0.5],\n                  [-2.0, 2.0], [1.0, -3.0]],\n  t_range=[0, 30],\n  ax_streamline(g1, g2, x, -4, 4, y, -4, 4),\n  title=\"Van der Pol Oscillator (mu=1): Limit Cycle\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 94,
      "outputs": [
        {
